# Architecture Style Guide
- Strictly enforce a decoupled architecture. Never write monolithic files.
- UI components (src/renderer/components) should stay small and single-purpose. ~250 lines is a smell-test guideline, not a hard cap - if a component is mixing unrelated concerns, extract sub-components regardless of length; a cohesive component a bit over 250 lines doesn't need to be split just to hit a number.
- All core application state changes must flow through custom hooks (src/renderer/hooks), never mixed directly inside UI markup.
- Static theme tables, hex colors, and type maps must sit in config files (src/renderer/config), not inline in utilities or views.
- Direct JSON fetch requests to pokeapi.co are mandatory. No web scraping or third-party scraper proxy middleware allowed.
- Use explicit TypeScript interfaces for all data contracts. Casting with 'as any' is forbidden unless handling external layout boundary wrappers.